        String name = null;
        if (name != null) {
            System.out.println(name.length());
        } else {
            System.out.println("Name is null");
        }
    }
}
```

### Option 2: Using a Ternary Operator

A more concise way to achieve the same result is by using a ternary operator:

```java
public class Main {
